sections.english:
Monks, these seven things lead to a lay follower’s decline. What are these seven? A lay follower neglects seeing monks, is heedless regarding listening to the True Dhamma, does not train in the higher morality, is largely lacking in confidence, listens to the Dhamma with a mind intent on finding fault, seeking shortcomings in monks—whether they are elders, new monks, or middle-ranking monks; seeks worthy recipients of offerings outside this teaching and to them makes prior offerings. Indeed, monks, these seven things lead to a lay follower’s decline.

Monks, these seven things lead to a lay follower’s non-decline. What are these seven? A lay follower does not neglect seeing monks, is not heedless regarding listening to the True Dhamma, trains in the higher morality, is largely full of confidence, listens to the Dhamma with a mind not intent on finding fault, not seeking shortcomings in monks—whether they are elders, new monks, or middle-ranking monks; does not seek worthy recipients of offerings outside this teaching and here makes prior offerings. Indeed, monks, these seven things lead to a lay follower’s non-decline. The Blessed One said this. Having said this, the Fortunate One, the Teacher, further said this:

The lay follower who neglects seeing those whose minds are cultivated,
And listening to the noble Dhamma, and does not train in the higher morality;
And whose lack of confidence in monks ever more increases;
And who desires to listen to the True Dhamma with a mind intent on finding fault;
And who seeks other worthy recipients of offerings outside of this teaching;
And there, that lay follower makes prior offerings.
Indeed, these seven factors of decline, well-expounded,
The lay follower who practices them declines from the True Dhamma.

The lay follower who does not neglect seeing those whose minds are cultivated,
And listening to the noble Dhamma, and trains in the higher morality;
And whose confidence in monks ever more increases;
And who desires to listen to the True Dhamma with a mind not intent on finding fault;
And who does not seek other worthy recipients of offerings outside of this teaching;
And here, that lay follower makes prior offerings.
Indeed, these seven factors of non-decline, well-expounded,
The lay follower who practices them does not decline from the True Dhamma.

Monks, there are these seven causes of a lay follower's progress. Which seven?

He does not neglect seeing monks; he is not heedless in listening to the true Dhamma; he trains in higher morality; he is abounding in serene faith; he listens to the Dhamma with a mind free from fault-finding towards monks—both elders, new monastics, and those in between—not seeking their flaws; he does not seek objects worthy of offerings outside this dispensation; and he makes his primary offering here within this dispensation.

The lay follower who neglects seeing those with cultivated minds, and listening to the Noble Dhamma, and does not train in higher morality;

And whose lack of serene faith in monks increasingly grows, and who desires to listen to the true Dhamma with a fault-finding mind;

And who seeks other objects worthy of offerings outside this dispensation, and makes his primary offering there;

These, indeed, are the seven qualities of decline, well-expounded; a lay follower who cultivates them falls away from the true Dhamma.

The lay follower who does not neglect seeing those with cultivated minds, and listening to the Noble Dhamma, and trains in higher morality;

And whose serene faith in monks increasingly grows, and who desires to listen to the true Dhamma with a mind free from fault-finding;

And who does not seek other objects worthy of offerings outside this dispensation, and makes his primary offering right here;

These, indeed, are the seven qualities of progress, well-expounded; a lay follower who cultivates them does not fall away from the true Dhamma.

sections.sinhala:
මහණෙනි, ගිහි උපාසකයාගේ පිරිහීමට කරුණු සතක් ඇත...පෙ... මහණෙනි, ගිහි උපාසකයාගේ දියුණුවට කරුණු සතක් ඇත. ඒ සත කවරේද? භාවිතාත්මයන්වූ භික්ෂූන් දැකීම අත්නොහරියි. සද්ධ‍ර්මය ශ‍්‍රවණය කිරීමෙහි නොපමාවෙයි. අධිශීලයෙහි පුහුණු වෙයි. බොහෝ ප‍්‍රසාදයෙන් යුක්ත වෙයි. මහළු, අලුත් හා මධ්‍යම භික්ෂූන් කෙරෙහි චෝදනා නොකරන සිතින්, දොස් සොයන්නෙක් නොවී, ධ‍ර්මය ශ‍්‍රවණය කරයි. මෙයින් පිටත අන් දක්ෂිණාවට සුදුස්සන් නොසොයයි. මෙහිම පළමුවෙන් පින් කරයි. මහණෙනි, උපාසකයාගේ දියුණුවට කරුණු සතක් නම් මේවාය.

යම් උපාසකයෙක්, භාවිතාත්මයන්වූ අරහතුන් වහන්සේලා දැකීම අත්හරින්නේද, ආර්ය ධ‍ර්මය ශ‍්‍රවණය නොකරයිද, අධිශීලයෙහි නොපුහුණු වෙයිද;

භික්ෂූන් කෙරෙහි අප‍්‍රසාදයද වඩ වඩාත් වැඩෙයිද, චෝදනා කරන සිතින් සද්ධ‍ර්මය ශ‍්‍රවණය කිරීමට කැමති වෙයිද;

මෙයින් පිටත අන් දක්ෂිණාවට සුදුස්සන් සොයයිද, එහිම පළමුවෙන් පින් කරයිද;

මෙසේ මනාකොට දේශනා කරන ලද පිරිහීමට හේතුවන මේ ධ‍ර්ම සත සේවනය කරන උපාසකයා සද්ධ‍ර්මයෙන් පිරිහෙයි.

යම් උපාසකයෙක්, භාවිතාත්මයන්වූ අරහතුන් වහන්සේලා දැකීම අත්නොහරින්නේද, ආර්ය ධ‍ර්මය ශ‍්‍රවණය කරයිද, අධිශීලයෙහි පුහුණු වෙයිද;

භික්ෂූන් කෙරෙහි ඔහුගේ ප‍්‍රසාදයද වඩ වඩාත් වැඩෙයිද, චෝදනා නොකරන සිතින් සද්ධ‍ර්මය ශ‍්‍රවණය කිරීමට කැමති වෙයිද;

මෙයින් පිටත අන් දක්ෂිණාවට සුදුස්සන් නොසොයයිද, මෙහිම පළමුවෙන් පින් කරයිද;

මෙසේ මනාකොට දේශනා කරන ලද නොපිරිහීමට හේතුවන මේ ධ‍ර්ම සත සේවනය කරන උපාසකයා සද්ධ‍ර්මයෙන් නොපිරිහෙයි.
